SIMPLE: idolize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idolize
<hw>I"dol*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Idolized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Idolizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To make an idol of; to pay idolatrous worship to; <as>as, to
<ex>idolize</ex> the sacred bull in Egypt</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To love to excess; to love or reverence to
adoration; <as>as, to <ex>idolize</ex> gold, children, a
hero</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idolize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Idolize
<hw>I"dol*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To practice idolatry.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>idolize</qex> after the manner of Egypt.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairbairn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idolizer</ent>⟦br⟧
